# WPForms Confirm Submission

Send a confirmation email to the user after form submission in WPForms.

## Description

This plugin allows you to send a confirmation email to the user who submitted a form using WPForms. The email contains a customized message confirming that their submission has been received.

## Installation

1. Upload the `wpforms-confirm-submission` folder to the `/wp-content/plugins/` directory.
2. Activate the plugin through the 'Plugins' menu in WordPress.

## Usage

1. Ensure that WPForms is installed and activated on your WordPress site.
2. Edit the plugin file (`wpforms-confirm-submission.php`) to customize the confirmation message if needed.
3. Submit a form created with WPForms to test the confirmation email functionality.

## Notes

- This plugin currently supports a single form (ID: 945). Modify the plugin code to support additional forms if needed.
- Ensure that your WordPress site is configured to send emails correctly.

